args: After being released, I chose to remain in\nthe Empire instead of returning home.
I wanted to learn more about the awful\nrumors of the ＂Shadewolves' leader.＂
As far as I knew, the Commander WAS\ntheir leader—but I couldn't ever imagine\nhim harming innocent people.
So where did all of these rumors\ncome from?
To find out the truth, I kept my eyes\nand ears open as I traveled.
Oy! You hear about the supply unit that\nstopped off at that village the other day?
The one wiped out by a hooded guy with\na sword? Yeah, I heard all about it.
Apparently he came back and torched the\nplace in the night. Cor, what a madman!
Sounds like an entire force of imperial\nsoldiers got wiped out on a ridge over\nthe mountain.
A guide from a nearby village ended up\ngetting crushed by rocks along with them.
I get that this guy wants revenge,\nbut why not just go after imperials?!
Now you mention it, I think this guy\nDID just target them—at first, anyway.
Yeah, I remember that.  Back when people\nwere saying he was a sword master with\nscars on his face.
Oh, it's you. New orders from HQ?
N-no. I wanted to ask if you know anything\nabout the ＂Shadewolves' leader.＂

This again? Look, I told you already—
some hooded guy is going around on a
revenge spree and killing anybody who
gets in his way.

Kinda funny how people change, eh?
Apparently the guy was ONLY targeting
imperials in the first little bit after the
Wolves were defeated.
Sure. Early on, everyone was talking\nabout the crazy guy who charged\nimperials without even hiding his face.
Not much. Apparently he was just some\ntough guy with scars on his face.
Then... Then when did he start hiding his\nface?
Hmm... Now that you mention it...
Sometimes he's got it covered and\nsometimes he doesn't...
What, a letter? Okay, lemme see...
＂After hearing uncountable rumors and\nyour testimony, I finally know the truth.＂
＂There are two different rumors circulating.\nOne is about a hooded man exacting\nrevenge without a care for the cost.＂
＂The other is about a man with scars on\nhis face who fights only imperial soldiers.＂
＂The two fight in very different ways.＂
＂Whenever something inhuman happens,\nthe hooded man is responsible.＂
＂But when imperials alone are attacked,\nthe fault lies with the scarred man.＂
＂One hides their face. The other does not.＂
You think there are TWO survivors from\nthe Shadewolves that are out there\nfighting the Empire?!
Huh. And somehow all those rumors just\nsort of smooshed into one big one?
I can't believe you worked that out.\nThat's pretty impressive!
B-but I have a favor to ask...
Please make sure that everyone\nknows the truth of these rumors!
Excellent work, Noelle. This concludes\nyour investigation into the Commander.
There has been a good deal of bad news,\nbut the mere fact he is alive is fortunate.
I know. It will not be possible for him\nto continue his mission.
I regret we will lose a means to sow chaos\nin the Empire, but there is nothing for it.
Here. Deliver this to the Commander and\nlet him know that he is to return at once.
Y-you tore up your orders again!
I'm not going back. I can't.
I abandoned everything in the name of\nrevenge—including my home and duty—\nyet now that revenge feels hopeless.
What future is there for a man\nwho has lost everything?
Everyone else is waiting for you at home,\nincluding Kirsty!
...Here. Give this blade and this sword to\nyour superior and tell them I died in my\nblind pursuit of vengeance.
Then never return to this land again.
Forget all that has happened and be free.\nThat is what I intend to do, and you would\nbe wise to follow my example.
I wanted to call out to him.\nI wanted to run after him.
But in the end, all I could do was watch\nas he disappeared into the distance.
